    <abstract>
      <t>This document defines a mechanism to indicate which traffic engineering protocols are enabled on a link in IS-IS. It does so by introducing a new traffic-engineering protocol sub-TLV for TLV-22. This document also describes mechanisms to address backward compatibility issues for implementations that have not yet been upgraded to software that understands this new sub-TLV.</t>
